Biography
In 1957, parents Alan S. Lorberbaum and Shirley Lorberbaum, founded Aladdin Mills, a manufacturer of rugs and bath mats. Jeffrey Lorberbaum started his career in 1976 when he joined the family business, Aladdin Mills. He served as the Vice President of Operations at Aladdin Mills from 1986 to 1994. In 1994, Aladdin Mills was acquired by Mohawk Industries for $387 million in stock. After the acquisition of Aladdin Mills by Mohawk Industries,  Lorberbaum was elected as the President and COO; later served as the President and ...
Contact us to see more Biography
