Contact us to see more Education History
Interesting Facts
In an interview, Lorberbaum once said, "The company was the family, and the family was the company; Every cent went back into the company to make it bigger, better, faster. Our only goal was to achieve as much growth as we could."
Contact us to see more Interesting Facts
Interests, Passion, Hobbies

Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Business
Description: Joined the family business Mohawk Industries in 1976; currently serves as the Chairman and CEO.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Philanthropy
Description: Active philanthropist is a Trustee of The Alan S. Lorberbaum Family Foundation; supports causes related to arts, healthcare, religious, education, child welfare and community development. 


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Politics
Description: Moderate political donor. Lifetime giving exceeds $57,000. 

Contact us to see more Interests, Passion, Hobbies
Philanthropy

Giving Profile: Trustee of The Alan S. Lorberbaum Family Foundation. In 2012, the foundation had assets exceeding $4 million and donated more than $400,000; gives primarily to arts, healthcare, religious, education, child welfare and community development causes. Recipients include: Allied Arts, Dalton State College, Creative Arts Guild, Brown University, the University of Georgia, the Boca Raton Museum of Art, McCallie School, Gettysburg Foundation, ArtsBuild, The Baylor School, Terry College of Business and WTCI.

